        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 9:28PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 928 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New Preston, or 10 miles northeast of New Milford, moving northeast
at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
West Torrington, Torringford, Hotchkissville, Haight Vineyard,
Pequabuck, Reynolds Bridge, Candlewood Trails, Pomeraug, Wrightville,
Harwinton, East Litchfield, Plymouth Green, Morris, Delano Field,
Dempsey Landing, Bethlehem Village, Candlewood Point, Litchfield
Green, Bethlehem, and Plymouth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to localized ponding of water in urban or poor drainage areas. Do
not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
